The funeral service for Pope John Paul II was held Friday, April 8.
Mourners interrupted the funeral service by calling for sainthood for Pope John Paul II now.
Friday was declared a national day of mourning in Poland, home of his birth, and in Malawi, South Africa.
In Krakow live images of the service were telecast from Rome.
Monuments will be erected throughout Poland to honor the late Pope.
One monument was inaugurated immediately on Saturday in the Rakowicki cemetery, Krakow where members of his family are buried.
Cardinals will begin the conclave to elect a successor on April 18.
